f=Brand Studio/nate/custom/experiment-backlog/SKILL.md · in=experiment-backlog nate's operating system: one prioritized queue growth experiments brand, ICE-scored (Impact Confidence Ease), run **one-or-few time** pre-registered success metrics, closed results log never loses lesson. Wins graduate rio standing campaigns, pulse's playbooks, lena's copy patterns, wherever win lives; losses get their cause recorded they aren't re-run amnesia (muse's registry discipline, applied experiments). · p=Growth work fails scattered enthusiasm: ten half-run tests, pre-registered metrics, wins nobody operationalized, losses re-attempted quarterly. backlog makes system: everything proposed gets scored, top item runs properly (the sibling ab-test-analysis skill enforces stats), result compounds. · wu=Triggers: "next experiment," "growth test," "add backlog," "what test," "what learn [test]." · st:/ Protocol=`Intake (ideas from muse, funnel-analysis' recommended experiments, rio/pulse/kai observations, \· the operator) → each becomes a backlog entry: hypothesis + metric + ICE score \· -> Prioritize: ICE descending; capacity honest (1–3 concurrent max; non-overlapping audiences) \· -> Run the top item: PRE-REGISTER metric + MDE + duration (ab-test-analysis' discipline) \· — no peeking, no mid-test goal-moving` · h3:Phase Intake Score=idea enters structured entry: **hypothesis** ("we believe [change] move [metric] because [reasoning]"), **one primary metric** guardrails), **ICE 1–10 each** Impact (if works, much needle move), Confidence (what evidence says flagged judgment rubric rule 0.6), Ease (effort run *valid* test, sloppy one). Ideas without falsifiable hypothesis back sharpening, queue. · h3:Phase Prioritize Honestly=ICE descending, two reality checks: **capacity** (running everything once tests nothing 1–3 concurrent, non-overlapping audiences/surfaces results don't contaminate) **dependency** test needing instrumentation kai doesn't gets blocked-status, silently skipped). · h3:Phase Run Pre-Registration=Before launch, entry locks: primary metric, minimum detectable effect, sample/duration plan (the sibling skill's math), decision rule ("if ship; stop"). Mid-test changes new experiment, edit discipline makes results mean something. · h3:Phase Close Compound=completed test gets: ab-test-analysis verdict, **lesson one honest line** (including "our hypothesis wrong because…"), decision. graduation protocol: shipped product/site wins owning surface; channel wins rio (standing campaign); content/hook wins pulse's register; copy wins lena. Losses archive cause; re-proposal archived loss say what changed. · of=`## Backlog: [brand] — [date] \·  \· \| # \| Hypothesis (one line) \| Metric \| I \| C \| E \| ICE \| Status \| \· \|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| \· [running / queued / blocked / done→ref]` · pr=**No falsifiable hypothesis, entry.**, **Pre-register didn't count.** Metric, MDE, duration, decision rule locked before launch; peeking (sibling skill's law)., **Few tests, run properly.** Capacity honesty beats activity theater., **Every result compounds.** Wins graduate owners; losses archive cause; amnesia re-runs caught intake., **ICE rubric** (rule 0.6) consistent prioritization, measurement; test itself measurement., **Guardrails ride test** primary-metric win degrades revenue/experience isn't win (sibling skill's table governs). · f=Empty backlog intake session: funnel-analysis' biggest leak standing first candidate., instrumentation metric blocked status instrumentation need routed kai; never run unmeasurable tests., Operator wants skip queue ("just try now") run it, still gets entry, pre-registration, logged result urgency skips queue, never discipline. · b:with Other Skills=`ab-test-analysis` (sibling) owns statistics; `funnel-analysis` (sibling) finds aim. skill owns queue, discipline, compounding., **muse** generates candidate ideas; **kai** supplies data/instrumentation receives results scorecard; **rio/pulse/lena** receive graduates; **vista's rice-prioritization** ranks roadmap features (different altitude features experiments); **board** gates any experiment whose spend crosses envelope.